  "local_port": 34998,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I stopped talking to girl completely whom I love after I got to know that she got engaged to a different guy. Now her marriage has been called off and I want to ask her out. How do I do it?",
  "response": "Navigating the situation you\u2019re in requires sensitivity and consideration of her feelings and circumstances. Here\u2019s a thoughtful approach to asking her out:\n\n1. **Re-establish Contact**: If you have not spoken in a while, start by reaching out in a friendly, non-romantic manner. You might say something like, \"Hey, it\u2019s been a while! How have you been?\"\n\n2. **Show Support**: Since she has gone through a significant emotional event, it\u2019s important to show empathy and offer support. You could express something like, \"I heard about your engagement being called off, I am really sorry that you had to go through that. If you ever need someone to talk to, I\u2019m here for you.\"\n\n3. **Gauge Her Response**: Listen to how she responds and what she says. If she opens up and seems comfortable talking with you, it may indicate she values your support. Follow her lead in the conversation and be attentive.\n\n4. **Take It Slow**: Given the recent events, it\u2019s wise to take things slowly. Don\u2019t rush into asking her out right away. Instead, build up the connection gradually. Spend time together as friends and see how she reacts.\n\n5. **Look for Signs**: Pay attention to any signs that she might be interested in a deeper connection. If she begins to spend more time with you or seems more engaged in conversations, it could be a positive sign.\n\n6. **Express Your Feelings**: When you feel the time is right, have an honest conversation about your feelings. Choose a moment when you\u2019re alone and there\u2019s no rush. You might say, \"I\u2019ve always cared a lot about you, and after everything, I realize that my feelings haven\u2019t changed. I would love to take you out and see where things might go between us.\"\n\n7. **Respect Her Space**: Regardless of her response, respect her feelings and space. She may need time to come to terms with her own emotions after her engagement. Be patient and understanding.\n\n8. **Be Prepared for Any Outcome**: Be mentally prepared for any answer, whether it\u2019s positive or not. Let her know that you value her friendship and want what\u2019s best for her, and that you respect her decision.\n\nIn summary, approach the situation with empathy, patience, and genuine care for her well-being. The most important thing is to ensure she feels comfortable and supported regardless of the outcome.",
